---++ Scope

The newsletter is to let people know specific things happening in OSG and to provide technical and practical information for readers, ie. what internet2 tools will be in VDT and when, what insight to using them is available and at what URL, etc...  Other parties are more than welcome to suggest idea&#39;s for upcoming articles.

Each technical brief should be no more than 100-120 words.

---++ Process


   * Chander and Ruth will assist in suggestions for articles based on Area Coordinator or other meetings.

   * First step will be to include the list of suggested articles at https://www.opensciencegrid.org/bin/view/Management/NewsletterArticles  and the text of all articles for the month will be kept by Jemise.
 
   * Jemise will press people for paragraphs about their activities and will receive paragraphs for editing.

   * Once uploaded Jemise will forward the articles to Clementine Jones who may do further editing (semantics and content; articles that are very long or out of scope will be sent back  to  the author.

   * Clemmie will upload the text to the opensciencegrid.org content management system - wordpress - and  send email to Jemise and Ruth. if extensive editing Clemmie to send to author, Ruth will edit and give comments, Ruth will re-send to Clemmie to make corrections.  

   * Once all articles are approved by Ruth, Clemmie will send to the Executive Board for approval - we give people about 24hours to review

   * Once uploaded on the web the newsletter will be sent out by the Grid Operations Center to osg@openscience.org and a reminder for Ruth Pordes to approve to be sent out.

---++ Including images

